# Deployment Patterns Overview

## Architecture

Our deployment architecture uses Coolify as the primary deployment platform:

- GitHub App integration for automated deployments
- Nixpacks for build optimization
- Preview environments for pull requests
- Zero-downtime deployments
- Automatic SSL/TLS certificates
- Real-time monitoring and logging

## Core Technologies

- Coolify for deployment automation
- GitHub App (@Coolify) for repository integration
- Nixpacks for build optimization
- Docker for containerization
- Built-in monitoring and logging

## Deployment Types

### 1. Production Deployments

- Manual approval required
- Zero-downtime updates
- Health checks enabled
- Force HTTPS
- Automatic SSL certificates
- Production domain routing

### 2. Staging Deployments

- Automatic deployments from develop
- Preview environments
- Health monitoring
- Staging domain routing
- Automated testing

### 3. Preview Deployments

- Automatic PR deployments
- Unique preview URLs
- Automatic cleanup
- Isolated environments
- Quick feedback loop

